/*
 * main.c - Sonic Mania (Saturn) entry point and game-state machine.
 *
 * The Green Hill foreground is a *streaming* VDP2 NBG1 cell-scroll plane drawing
 * the full 16384x2048 level: all unique 8x8 cells stay resident in VRAM, and a
 * 64x64-cell page (one PL_SIZE_1x1 plane = 512x512px) is rebuilt in Work RAM and
 * pushed to VRAM each frame via SCU DMA (slDMACopy) as the camera pans.
 *
 * Why DMA: VDP2 VRAM written by the CPU during active display does not reliably
 * reach the screen, so per-frame page updates via CPU stores fail. The official
 * SGL 2D-scroll sample (NOV96 DTS SGL302/SAMPLE2/SEGA2D_1) uploads cells and the
 * pattern-name map to VRAM with slDMACopy; we use the same mechanism every frame.
 */
